<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="463" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1362,2570,1222,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1363,1498,1663,1688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="463">Breeding.</emphasis>
There is no specific information available for this species, but all titis form monogamous breeding pairs. The male provides parental care by carrying the single offspring.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
